It exits the VNC via the cervical connective (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Within the VNC it fasciculates with the median dorsal abdominal tract (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It receives input in the T1 leg neuropil and intermediate tectulum and sends output to the brain (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is glutamate (Eckstein et al., 2024). There is approximately one of these cells per organism with its soma in the prothoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).

value.value: Adult descending neuron (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It enters the VNC via the cervical connective (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its morphology in the brain is similar to that of the female oviDN neurons, forming a loop in the superior brain, crossing the midline above the esophagus, arborizing lateral to the esophagus and entering the cervical connective on the contralateral side (Sturner et al., 2024). Within the VNC it fasciculates with the median dorsal abdominal tract and forms no significant arbors until reaching the abdominal neuromere, where it has presynapses (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024).

value.value: Adult sensory neuron that enters the brain via the maxillary-labial nerve and arborizes in the gnathal ganglion (Dorkenwald et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024). It descends to the ventral nerve cord and follows the ventral median tract of ventral cervical fasciculus (Takemura et al., 2023; Sturner et al., 2024). It sends output to the T1 leg neuropil (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There is one of these cells on each side (Sturner et al., 2024).
